            <h3>2. Komodo Islands (NTT)</h3>
            <p>Komodo island, part of the Lesser Sunda chain of Indonesian islands, is the rugged habitat 
                of the 3m-long Komodo dragon monitor lizard. Komodo National Park covers the entire region and is 
                home to more than 4,000 dragons, and is made up of rusty-red volcanic hills, savannah and forests. 
                Its surrounding waters of seagrass beds, mangrove shrublands and coral reefs are famous for diving.
                </p>
            
        </div>

