            <h3>5. Lawang Sewu (Jawa Tengah)</h3>
            <p>Lawang Sewu, literally Thousand Doors, is a landmark in Semarang, Central Java, Indonesia, built as the headquarters of the Dutch East Indies Railway Company. The colonial era building is famous as a haunted house, though the Semarang city government has attempted to rebrand it. 
            </p>
            
